        "type": "p",
        "text": "That old *I*, the one that took over when Adam sinned, the self that treated God as an enemy, has been dethroned, displaced, destroyed. So you no longer have a nature that craves and desires sin. You are no longer a sinner by nature. When you still feel like one, remember the devil is a liar. Do not reckon by the natural. Keep counting the old *I* dead."
